{"nbformat":4,"nbformat_minor":0,"metadata":{"colab":{"provenance":[{"file_id":"1XQPEP1IWCKQzMOtlUCLa3A2IRVxsd2qp","timestamp":1779740900964}],"gpuType":"T4"},"kernelspec":{"name":"python3","display_name":"Python 3"},"language_info":{"name":"python"}},"cells":[{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["# Patch Extraction Pipeline\n","\n","This pipeline is designed for extracting 128x128 pixel patches for UNet training from 16-band GeoTIFF imagery and corresponding vector polygons.\n","\n","## Key Features:\n","-   **Memory-Efficient**: Reads raster data in windows, avoiding loading the full image into RAM.\n","-   **Output**: Saves extracted patches directly to Google Drive as `.npy` files.\n","-   **Data Split**: Automatically divides patches into training, validation, and test sets.\n","-   **Class Field**: Defines labels as: 0 = unburned, 1 = burned, 255 = ignore.\n","-   **Spatial Split**: Ensures train, validation, and test zones do not overlap spatially.\n","\n","## Spatial Layout (Configurable):\n","```\n","|<----- train (70%) ----->|<- val (15%) ->|<- test (15%) ->|\n","```\n","By default, columns are split along the WIDTH axis (`SPLIT_AXIS = \"cols\"`). This can be changed to `\"rows\"` to split along the HEIGHT axis.\n","\n","## Configurable Input Stack:\n","-   **PlanetScope**: Channels selected via `PS_BANDS`.\n","-   **Sentinel-2**: Pre- and post-fire channels selected via `S2_BANDS`.\n","-   **Landsat**: Pre- and post-fire channels selected via `LS_BANDS`.\n","-   **Indices**: Options to include `USE_NDVI`, `USE_NBR`, and `USE_DELTA` (dNDVI, dNBR).\n","\n","## Example Final Stack:\n","-   13 (PS) + 5 (S2 pre) + 5 (S2 post) + 2 (NDVI) + 2 (NBR) + 2 (delta) = 29 channels."],"metadata":{"id":"bgUJmT0EH72K"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["# ⚙️ Configuration (set the parameters)"],"metadata":{"id":"fP8zRySZIys8"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["# ─────────────────────────────────────────────\n","# CONFIG  –  edit these parameters\n","# ─────────────────────────────────────────────\n","\n","PROJECT_ROOT = \"/content/drive/MyDrive/U-Net_burned_areas_project\"\n","\n","USE_SENTINEL = True # Flag to enable Sentinel processing (make sure that images are already downloaded)\n","USE_LANDSAT = False # Flag to enable Landsat processing (make sure that images are already downloaded)\n","\n","SITE_LIST = [\n","    'site-432-tropical-savanna',\n","    'site-682-tropical-savanna',\n","    # add more if you want\n","]\n","\n","NAME_PATCH_FOLDER = 'patches_PS_SENT_432_682' # or patches_PS16_only etc\n","\n","# ─────────────────────────────────────────────\n","# CONFIG — PlanetScope band selection (1-based)\n","# ─────────────────────────────────────────────\n","# 01:blue-pre  02:green-pre  03:red-pre   04:nir-pre   05:ndvi-pre  06:BAI-pre\n","# 07:blue-post 08:green-post 09:red-post  10:nir-post  11:ndvi-post 12:BAI-post\n","# 13:slope     14:aspect     15:curvature 16:landscape\n","PS_BANDS = [2, 3, 4, 5, 6,\n","            8, 9, 10, 11, 12,\n","            13, 14, 15,\n","            16]\n","# Set to None to use all bands: PS_BANDS = None\n","\n","# ─────────────────────────────────────────────\n","# CONFIG — Sentinel-2\n","# ─────────────────────────────────────────────\n","\n","\n","# Bands from each S2 image (1-based indices in the file)\n","# B5=RedEdge1, B6=RedEdge2, B7=RedEdge3, B11=SWIR1, B12=SWIR2\n","S2_BANDS = [5, 6, 7, 11, 12]\n","\n","\n","# Bands for index calculation (1-based in S2 file)\n","# NDVI = (NIR - Red) / (NIR + Red)\n","# NBR  = (NIR - SWIR2) / (NIR + SWIR2)\n","S2_NIR_BAND  = 8    # B8\n","S2_RED_BAND  = 4    # B4\n","S2_SWIR_BAND = 12   # B12\n","\n","# ─────────────────────────────────────────────\n","# CONFIG — Landsat (New Section)\n","# ─────────────────────────────────────────────\n","# Example bands for Landsat 8/9 (adjust based on your specific Landsat data)\n","# B2=Blue, B3=Green, B4=Red, B5=NIR, B6=SWIR1, B7=SWIR2\n","LS_BANDS = [2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7]\n","\n","# Bands for index calculation (1-based in LS file)\n","LS_NIR_BAND  = 5    # Band 5\n","LS_RED_BAND  = 4    # Band 4\n","LS_SWIR_BAND = 7   # Band 7\n","\n","# ─────────────────────────────────────────────\n","# CONFIG — indices (calculated from S2/LS)\n","# ─────────────────────────────────────────────\n","USE_NDVI  = True   # NDVI_pre, NDVI_post\n","USE_NBR   = True   # NBR_pre,  NBR_post\n","USE_DELTA = True   # dNDVI = NDVI_post - NDVI_pre\n","                   # dNBR  = NBR_pre   - NBR_post  (standard dNBR sign)\n","\n","PATCH_SIZE = 128\n","STRIDE     = 128     # stride < PATCH_SIZE → overlap within each zone\n","IGNORE_VAL = 255\n","\n","# Minimum share of labeled pixels (not 255) for a patch to be kept\n","MIN_VALID_RATIO = 0.70\n","\n","# Spatial split ratios (must sum to 1.0)\n","SPLIT_RATIOS = {\"train\": 0.70, \"val\": 0.15, \"test\": 0.15}\n","\n","# Axis along which the image is divided into zones: \"cols\" or \"rows\"\n","SPLIT_AXIS = \"cols\"\n","\n","RANDOM_SEED = 42"],"metadata":{"id":"H7uoUeV01AoM"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["#⏳ Creation of patches... (run all the cells)"],"metadata":{"id":"5idYvXXcLdDy"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["import gc\n","import json\n","import numpy as np\n","import geopandas as gpd\n","import rasterio\n","from rasterio.features import rasterize\n","from rasterio.windows import Window\n","from rasterio.enums import Resampling\n","from rasterio.warp import reproject\n","from pathlib import Path\n","from tqdm import tqdm"],"metadata":{"id":"EqzuQ43n06b5"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["PROJECT_ROOT = Path(PROJECT_ROOT)"],"metadata":{"id":"3WUSeCVF1oBZ"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["# ─────────────────────────────────────────────\n","# HELPERS — indices\n","# ─────────────────────────────────────────────\n","\n","def compute_ndvi(nir: np.ndarray, red: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n","    return (nir - red) / (nir + red + 1e-8)\n","\n","def compute_nbr(nir: np.ndarray, swir: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n","    return (nir - swir) / (nir + swir + 1e-8)"],"metadata":{"id":"vldqUHwrq_O-"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["# ─────────────────────────────────────────────\n","# HELPERS — S2 → PS resampling\n","# ─────────────────────────────────────────────\n","\n","def resample_band(s2_src, band_idx: int, ps_src) -> np.ndarray:\n","    \"\"\"Resamples a single S2 band to PS size and projection.\"\"\"\n","    out = np.empty((ps_src.height, ps_src.width), dtype=np.float32)\n","    reproject(\n","        source        = rasterio.band(s2_src, band_idx),\n","        destination   = out,\n","        src_transform = s2_src.transform,\n","        src_crs       = s2_src.crs,\n","        dst_transform = ps_src.transform,\n","        dst_crs       = ps_src.crs,\n","        resampling    = Resampling.cubic,\n","    )\n","    return out\n","\n","\n","def read_s2_snapshot(s2_path: str, ps_src,\n","                     stack_bands: list,\n","                     nir_band: int,\n","                     red_band: int,\n","                     swir_band: int):\n","    \"\"\"\n","    Reads one S2 snapshot:\n","      - resamples stack_bands → (N, H, W)\n","      - resamples NIR, Red, SWIR for indices\n","    Returns:\n","      stack  : (N, H, W) float32  — channels for the stack\n","      nir    : (H, W) float32\n","      red    : (H, W) float32\n","      swir   : (H, W) float32\n","    \"\"\"\n","    with rasterio.open(s2_path) as s2_src:\n","        # All unique bands to read\n","        needed = set(stack_bands) | {nir_band, red_band, swir_band}\n","        cache  = {}\n","        for b in needed:\n","            cache[b] = resample_band(s2_src, b, ps_src)\n","\n","    stack = np.stack([cache[b] for b in stack_bands], axis=0)  # (N, H, W)\n","    return stack, cache[nir_band], cache[red_band], cache[swir_band]"],"metadata":{"id":"iLVr7sZbou3i"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["# ─────────────────────────────────────────────\n","# HELPERS — misc\n","# ─────────────────────────────────────────────\n","\n","def load_vector(gpkg_path: str, raster_crs) -> gpd.GeoDataFrame:\n","    gdf = gpd.read_file(gpkg_path)\n","    if gdf.crs != raster_crs:\n","        gdf = gdf.to_crs(raster_crs)\n","    return gdf\n","\n","\n","def rasterize_labels(gdf, transform, height, width) -> np.ndarray:\n","    mask     = np.full((height, width), IGNORE_VAL, dtype=np.uint8)\n","    burned   = [(g, 1) for g in gdf[gdf[\"Class\"] == 1].geometry if g is not None]\n","    unburned = [(g, 0) for g in gdf[gdf[\"Class\"] == 0].geometry if g is not None]\n","    if burned:\n","        rasterize(burned,   out=mask, transform=transform, fill=IGNORE_VAL, dtype=np.uint8)\n","    if unburned:\n","        rasterize(unburned, out=mask, transform=transform, fill=IGNORE_VAL, dtype=np.uint8)\n","    return mask\n","\n","\n","def normalize_patch(patch: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n","    \"\"\"Per-channel min-max [0,1]. Input: (C, H, W).\"\"\"\n","    out = np.empty_like(patch, dtype=np.float32)\n","    for c in range(patch.shape[0]):\n","        ch = patch[c]\n","        mn, mx = ch.min(), ch.max()\n","        out[c] = (ch - mn) / (mx - mn + 1e-8)\n","    return out\n","\n","\n","def compute_spatial_zones(total: int, ratios: dict) -> dict:\n","    assert abs(sum(ratios.values()) - 1.0) < 1e-6\n","    n_train = int(total * ratios[\"train\"])\n","    n_val   = int(total * ratios[\"val\"])\n","    def snap(v):\n","        return (v // PATCH_SIZE) * PATCH_SIZE\n","    t_end = snap(n_train)\n","    v_end = snap(n_train + n_val)\n","    return {\n","        \"train\": (0,     t_end),\n","        \"val\":   (t_end, v_end),\n","        \"test\":  (v_end, total),\n","    }\n","\n","\n","# ─────────────────────────────────────────────\n","# MAIN\n","# ─────────────────────────────────────────────\n","\n","def extract_patches(NUM_SITE: int):\n","    np.random.seed(RANDOM_SEED)\n","\n","    for split in (\"train\", \"val\", \"test\"):\n","        for sub in (\"images\", \"labels\"):\n","            (Path(OUT_DIR) / split / sub).mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n","\n","    # ── PlanetScope ───────────────────────────\n","    ps_src  = rasterio.open(PS_PATH)\n","    H, W    = ps_src.height, ps_src.width\n","    crs     = ps_src.crs\n","    tf      = ps_src.transform\n","    ps_read = PS_BANDS if PS_BANDS is not None else list(range(1, ps_src.count + 1))\n","    print(f\"PlanetScope: {W}×{H} px, reading bands {ps_read}\")\n","\n","    # ── Sentinel-2 (full resampling in advance) ─\n","    extra_layers = []   # list of (H,W) arrays to add to the stack\n","    index_info   = {}   # for metadata\n","\n","    if USE_SENTINEL:\n","        print(\"\\nReading pre-fire Sentinel-2 …\")\n","        s2_pre_stack, nir_pre, red_pre, swir_pre = read_s2_snapshot(\n","            S2_PRE_PATH, ps_src, S2_BANDS, S2_NIR_BAND, S2_RED_BAND, S2_SWIR_BAND)\n","\n","        print(\"Reading post-fire Sentinel-2 …\")\n","        s2_post_stack, nir_post, red_post, swir_post = read_s2_snapshot(\n","            S2_POST_PATH, ps_src, S2_BANDS, S2_NIR_BAND, S2_RED_BAND, S2_SWIR_BAND)\n","\n","        # S2 channels into stack\n","        s2_full = np.concatenate([s2_pre_stack, s2_post_stack], axis=0)  # (2N, H, W)\n","        extra_layers.append(s2_full)\n","        print(f\"  S2 channels in stack: {s2_full.shape[0]} ({len(S2_BANDS)} pre + {len(S2_BANDS)} post)\")\n","\n","        # Indices (calculated from S2)\n","        # Note: These indices will be calculated regardless of USE_LANDSAT if USE_SENTINEL is True\n","        s2_index_layers = []\n","\n","        if USE_NDVI:\n","            ndvi_s2_pre  = compute_ndvi(nir_pre,  red_pre)\n","            ndvi_s2_post = compute_ndvi(nir_post, red_post)\n","            s2_index_layers += [ndvi_s2_pre, ndvi_s2_post]\n","            index_info[\"NDVI_S2_pre\"]  = True\n","            index_info[\"NDVI_S2_post\"] = True\n","\n","        if USE_NBR:\n","            nbr_s2_pre  = compute_nbr(nir_pre,  swir_pre)\n","            nbr_s2_post = compute_nbr(nir_post, swir_post)\n","            s2_index_layers += [nbr_s2_pre, nbr_s2_post]\n","            index_info[\"NBR_S2_pre\"]  = True\n","            index_info[\"NBR_S2_post\"] = True\n","\n","        if USE_DELTA:\n","            if USE_NDVI: # dNDVI from S2\n","                dndvi_s2 = ndvi_s2_post - ndvi_s2_pre\n","                s2_index_layers.append(dndvi_s2)\n","                index_info[\"dNDVI_S2\"] = True\n","            if USE_NBR: # dNBR from S2 (standard sign)\n","                dnbr_s2 = nbr_s2_pre  - nbr_s2_post\n","                s2_index_layers.append(dnbr_s2)\n","                index_info[\"dNBR_S2\"] = True\n","\n","        if s2_index_layers:\n","            idx_s2_array = np.stack(s2_index_layers, axis=0)  # (K, H, W)\n","            extra_layers.append(idx_s2_array)\n","            print(f\"  S2 Indices in stack: {idx_s2_array.shape[0]}  {list(k for k in index_info.keys() if 'S2' in k)}\")\n","\n","        # Freeing memory from temporary S2 arrays\n","        del nir_pre, red_pre, swir_pre, nir_post, red_post, swir_post\n","        del s2_pre_stack, s2_post_stack\n","        if s2_index_layers:\n","            del s2_index_layers\n","        gc.collect()\n","\n","    # New: Landsat (full resampling in advance)\n","    if USE_LANDSAT:\n","        print(\"\\nReading pre-fire Landsat …\")\n","        ls_pre_stack, nir_ls_pre, red_ls_pre, swir_ls_pre = read_s2_snapshot(\n","            LS_PRE_PATH, ps_src, LS_BANDS, LS_NIR_BAND, LS_RED_BAND, LS_SWIR_BAND)\n","\n","        print(\"Reading post-fire Landsat …\")\n","        ls_post_stack, nir_ls_post, red_ls_post, swir_ls_post = read_s2_snapshot(\n","            LS_POST_PATH, ps_src, LS_BANDS, LS_NIR_BAND, LS_RED_BAND, LS_SWIR_BAND)\n","\n","        # Landsat channels into stack\n","        ls_full = np.concatenate([ls_pre_stack, ls_post_stack], axis=0)  # (2N, H, W)\n","        extra_layers.append(ls_full)\n","        print(f\"  Landsat channels in stack: {ls_full.shape[0]} ({len(LS_BANDS)} pre + {len(LS_BANDS)} post)\")\n","\n","        # Indices (calculated from Landsat)\n","        ls_index_layers = []\n","\n","        if USE_NDVI:\n","            ndvi_ls_pre  = compute_ndvi(nir_ls_pre,  red_ls_pre)\n","            ndvi_ls_post = compute_ndvi(nir_ls_post, red_ls_post)\n","            ls_index_layers += [ndvi_ls_pre, ndvi_ls_post]\n","            index_info[\"NDVI_LS_pre\"]  = True\n","            index_info[\"NDVI_LS_post\"] = True\n","\n","        if USE_NBR:\n","            nbr_ls_pre  = compute_nbr(nir_ls_pre,  swir_ls_pre)\n","            nbr_ls_post = compute_nbr(nir_ls_post, swir_ls_post)\n","            ls_index_layers += [nbr_ls_pre, nbr_ls_post]\n","            index_info[\"NBR_LS_pre\"]  = True\n","            index_info[\"NBR_LS_post\"] = True\n","\n","        if USE_DELTA:\n","            if USE_NDVI: # dNDVI from LS\n","                dndvi_ls = ndvi_ls_post - ndvi_ls_pre\n","                ls_index_layers.append(dndvi_ls)\n","                index_info[\"dNDVI_LS\"] = True\n","            if USE_NBR: # dNBR from LS (standard sign)\n","                dnbr_ls = nbr_ls_pre  - nbr_ls_post\n","                ls_index_layers.append(dnbr_ls)\n","                index_info[\"dNBR_LS\"] = True\n","\n","        if ls_index_layers:\n","            idx_ls_array = np.stack(ls_index_layers, axis=0)  # (K, H, W)\n","            extra_layers.append(idx_ls_array)\n","            print(f\"  Landsat Indices in stack: {idx_ls_array.shape[0]}  {list(k for k in index_info.keys() if 'LS' in k)}\")\n","\n","        # Freeing memory from temporary Landsat arrays\n","        del nir_ls_pre, red_ls_pre, swir_ls_pre, nir_ls_post, red_ls_post, swir_ls_post\n","        del ls_pre_stack, ls_post_stack\n","        if ls_index_layers:\n","            del ls_index_layers\n","        gc.collect()\n","\n","    # Collect extra into one array (H, W, ...) for fast patch slicing\n","    extra_full = np.concatenate(extra_layers, axis=0) if extra_layers else None  # (M, H, W)\n","\n","    total_bands = len(ps_read) + (extra_full.shape[0] if extra_full is not None else 0)\n","    print(f\"\\nTotal channels in stack: {total_bands}\")\n","\n","    # ── Labels ────────────────────────────────\n","    print(\"\\nRasterizing labels …\")\n","    gdf        = load_vector(GPKG_PATH, crs)\n","    label_full = rasterize_labels(gdf, tf, H, W)\n","    del gdf; gc.collect()\n","    print(f\"Unique label values: {np.unique(label_full)}\")\n","\n","    # ── Spatial zones ─────────────────────────\n","    dim        = W if SPLIT_AXIS == \"cols\" else H\n","    zones      = compute_spatial_zones(dim, SPLIT_RATIOS)\n","    print(f\"\\nSpatial zones ({SPLIT_AXIS}): \"\n","          + \"  \".join(f\"{k}=[{v[0]},{v[1]})\" for k, v in zones.items()))\n","\n","    # ── Extract patches ───────────────────────\n","    counters = {\"train\": 0, \"val\": 0, \"test\": 0}\n","\n","    for split_name, (zone_start, zone_end) in zones.items():\n","        print(f\"\\nProcessing '{split_name}' …\")\n","        out_img = Path(OUT_DIR) / split_name / \"images\"\n","        out_lbl = Path(OUT_DIR) / split_name / \"labels\"\n","\n","        if SPLIT_AXIS == \"cols\":\n","            row_range = range(0, H - PATCH_SIZE + 1, STRIDE)\n","            col_range = range(zone_start, zone_end - PATCH_SIZE + 1, STRIDE)\n","        else:\n","            row_range = range(zone_start, zone_end - PATCH_SIZE + 1, STRIDE)\n","            col_range = range(0, W - PATCH_SIZE + 1, STRIDE)\n","\n","        patch_list = [(r, c) for r in row_range for c in col_range]\n","        idx = 0\n","\n","        for row_off, col_off in tqdm(patch_list, desc=split_name, unit=\"patch\"):\n","            lp = label_full[row_off:row_off + PATCH_SIZE,\n","                            col_off:col_off + PATCH_SIZE]\n","            if np.sum(lp != IGNORE_VAL) / lp.size < MIN_VALID_RATIO:\n","                continue\n","\n","            # PS: read only the required window from disk\n","            window   = Window(col_off, row_off, PATCH_SIZE, PATCH_SIZE)\n","            ps_patch = ps_src.read(ps_read, window=window).astype(np.float32)  # (C_ps, P, P)\n","\n","            if extra_full is not None:\n","                ex_patch = extra_full[:,\n","                                      row_off:row_off + PATCH_SIZE,\n","                                      col_off:col_off + PATCH_SIZE]             # (M, P, P)\n","                img_patch = np.concatenate([ps_patch, ex_patch], axis=0)\n","            else:\n","                img_patch = ps_patch\n","\n","            img_patch = normalize_patch(img_patch)\n","\n","            np.save(out_img / f\"{idx:06d}.npy\", img_patch)\n","            np.save(out_lbl / f\"{idx:06d}.npy\", lp.copy())\n","            idx += 1\n","\n","        counters[split_name] = idx\n","        print(f\"  Saved: {idx} patches\")\n","\n","    ps_src.close()\n","\n","    # ── Metadata ──────────────────────────────\n","    # Calculate n_classes based on unique values in label_full, excluding IGNORE_VAL\n","    unique_labels = np.unique(label_full[label_full != IGNORE_VAL])\n","    n_classes = len(unique_labels)\n","\n","    meta = {\n","        \"patch_size\":       PATCH_SIZE,\n","        \"stride\":           STRIDE,\n","        \"n_bands_total\":    total_bands,\n","        \"ps_bands\":         ps_read,\n","        \"use_sentinel\":     USE_SENTINEL,\n","        \"s2_bands\":         S2_BANDS         if USE_SENTINEL else [],\n","        \"use_landsat\":      USE_LANDSAT, # New: Landsat info\n","        \"ls_bands\":         LS_BANDS         if USE_LANDSAT else [],\n","        \"indices\":          index_info,\n","        \"ignore_value\":     IGNORE_VAL,\n","        \"min_valid_ratio\":  MIN_VALID_RATIO,\n","        \"split_ratios\":     SPLIT_RATIOS,\n","        \"split_axis\":       SPLIT_AXIS,\n","        \"counts\":           counters,\n","        \"n_classes\":        n_classes\n","    }\n","    with open(Path(OUT_DIR) / \"metadata.json\", \"w\") as f:\n","        json.dump(meta, f, indent=2)\n","\n","    total = sum(counters.values())\n","    print(f\"\\n✅  Done for the {NUM_SITE} site! Total patches: {total}\")\n","    for s, n in counters.items():\n","        pct = n / total * 100 if total else 0\n","        print(f\"   {s:5s}: {n:5d}  ({pct:.1f}%)\")\n","    print(f\"\\nChannels per patch: {total_bands}\")\n","    print(f\"Saved to:     {OUT_DIR}\")\n","    print(f\"\\nFor model: UNet(in_channels={total_bands}, out_channels={n_classes})\")"],"metadata":{"id":"zz4-j8zd03ti"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","metadata":{"id":"1045ead3"},"source":["def slice_image_for_prediction(image: np.ndarray, patch_size: int) -> list[np.ndarray]:\n","    \"\"\"\n","    Slices an image into non-overlapping patches of a specified size for prediction.\n","    Handles cases where image dimensions are not perfectly divisible by patch_size\n","    by padding the image.\n","\n","    Args:\n","        image (np.ndarray): The input image array (channels, height, width).\n","        patch_size (int): The desired size of the square patches.\n","\n","    Returns:\n","        list[np.ndarray]: A list of non-overlapping image patches.\n","    \"\"\"\n","    C, H, W = image.shape\n","    patches = []\n","\n","    # Calculate padding needed\n","    pad_h = (patch_size - (H % patch_size)) % patch_size\n","    pad_w = (patch_size - (W % patch_size)) % patch_size\n","\n","    # Pad the image\n","    padded_image = np.pad(image, ((0, 0), (0, pad_h), (0, pad_w)), mode='reflect')\n","\n","    # Update dimensions after padding\n","    _, padded_H, padded_W = padded_image.shape\n","\n","    for r in range(0, padded_H, patch_size):\n","        for c in range(0, padded_W, patch_size):\n","            patch = padded_image[:, r:r + patch_size, c:c + patch_size]\n","            patches.append(patch)\n","\n","    return patches"],"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"601f8420"},"source":["### Demonstration of `slice_image_for_prediction`"]},{"cell_type":"code","metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"116d3728","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1780846754977,"user_tz":-120,"elapsed":8,"user":{"displayName":"Evgenii Miasnikov","userId":"16558642990374440926"}},"outputId":"b5ab1259-4ff9-4227-9a80-77bba1fa2feb"},"source":["# Create a dummy image for demonstration: (channels, height, width)\n","dummy_image = np.arange(3 * 250 * 250).reshape(3, 250, 250).astype(np.float32)\n","print(f\"Original image shape: {dummy_image.shape}\")\n","\n","# Define patch size\n","demo_patch_size = 128\n","\n","# Slice the image\n","demo_patches = slice_image_for_prediction(dummy_image, demo_patch_size)\n","\n","print(f\"Number of patches extracted: {len(demo_patches)}\")\n","if demo_patches:\n","    print(f\"Shape of each patch: {demo_patches[0].shape}\")\n","    # Verify that the first patch has content from the original image\n","    # For a simple check, compare a corner of the first patch with the original image\n","    original_corner = dummy_image[0, :demo_patch_size, :demo_patch_size]\n","    patch_corner = demo_patches[0][0, :, :]\n","    print(f\"First 5x5 pixels of original image (channel 0):\\n{original_corner[:5,:5]}\")\n","    print(f\"First 5x5 pixels of first patch (channel 0):\\n{patch_corner[:5,:5]}\")"],"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Original image shape: (3, 250, 250)\n","Number of patches extracted: 4\n","Shape of each patch: (3, 128, 128)\n","First 5x5 pixels of original image (channel 0):\n","[[0.000e+00 1.000e+00 2.000e+00 3.000e+00 4.000e+00]\n"," [2.500e+02 2.510e+02 2.520e+02 2.530e+02 2.540e+02]\n"," [5.000e+02 5.010e+02 5.020e+02 5.030e+02 5.040e+02]\n"," [7.500e+02 7.510e+02 7.520e+02 7.530e+02 7.540e+02]\n"," [1.000e+03 1.001e+03 1.002e+03 1.003e+03 1.004e+03]]\n","First 5x5 pixels of first patch (channel 0):\n","[[0.000e+00 1.000e+00 2.000e+00 3.000e+00 4.000e+00]\n"," [2.500e+02 2.510e+02 2.520e+02 2.530e+02 2.540e+02]\n"," [5.000e+02 5.010e+02 5.020e+02 5.030e+02 5.040e+02]\n"," [7.500e+02 7.510e+02 7.520e+02 7.530e+02 7.540e+02]\n"," [1.000e+03 1.001e+03 1.002e+03 1.003e+03 1.004e+03]]\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["if __name__ == \"__main__\":\n","    try:\n","        from google.colab import drive\n","        drive.mount(\"/content/drive\")\n","    except Exception:\n","        pass\n","\n","    for SITE_FULL_NAME in SITE_LIST:\n","        # Extract numerical site ID from the full name (e.g., 432 from 'site-432-tropical-savanna')\n","        NUM_SITE = int(SITE_FULL_NAME.split('-')[1])\n","\n","        GPKG_PATH  = f\"{PROJECT_ROOT}/data/sites/{SITE_FULL_NAME}/{NUM_SITE}_polygons.gpkg\"\n","        OUT_DIR    = f\"{PROJECT_ROOT}/data/sites/{SITE_FULL_NAME}/patches/{NAME_PATCH_FOLDER}\"   # will be created if absent\n","\n","        # ──────────────────────────────\n","        # INPUT RASTERS\n","        # ──────────────────────────────\n","\n","        PS_PATH = f\"{PROJECT_ROOT}/data/sites/{SITE_FULL_NAME}/{NUM_SITE}_predictors.tif\"\n","\n","        S2_PRE_PATH = f\"{PROJECT_ROOT}/data/sites/{SITE_FULL_NAME}/Sentinel/Sentinel_PRE.tif\"\n","\n","        S2_POST_PATH = f\"{PROJECT_ROOT}/data/sites/{SITE_FULL_NAME}/Sentinel/Sentinel_POST.tif\"\n","\n","        # New: Landsat paths\n","        LS_PRE_PATH = f\"{PROJECT_ROOT}/data/sites/{SITE_FULL_NAME}/Landsat/Landsat_PRE.tif\"\n","        LS_POST_PATH = f\"{PROJECT_ROOT}/data/sites/{SITE_FULL_NAME}/Landsat/Landsat_POST.tif\"\n","\n","        extract_patches(NUM_SITE)"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"_elShLHa3lkX","outputId":"5435122a-f96f-41ae-ac17-2dcdb7a7e123","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1780847187009,"user_tz":-120,"elapsed":432031,"user":{"displayName":"Evgenii Miasnikov","userId":"16558642990374440926"}}},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Mounted at /content/drive\n","PlanetScope: 8789×6124 px, reading bands [2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 8, 9, 10, 11, 12, 13, 14, 15, 16]\n","\n","Reading pre-fire Sentinel-2 …\n","Reading post-fire Sentinel-2 …\n","  S2 channels in stack: 10 (5 pre + 5 post)\n","  S2 Indices in stack: 6  ['NDVI_S2_pre', 'NDVI_S2_post', 'NBR_S2_pre', 'NBR_S2_post', 'dNDVI_S2', 'dNBR_S2']\n","\n","Total channels in stack: 30\n","\n","Rasterizing labels …\n","Unique label values: [  0   1 255]\n","\n","Spatial zones (cols): train=[0,6144)  val=[6144,7424)  test=[7424,8789)\n","\n","Processing 'train' …\n"]},{"output_type":"stream","name":"stderr","text":["train: 100%|██████████| 2256/2256 [01:37<00:00, 23.23patch/s] \n"]},{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["  Saved: 1602 patches\n","\n","Processing 'val' …\n"]},{"output_type":"stream","name":"stderr","text":["val: 100%|██████████| 470/470 [00:25<00:00, 18.28patch/s]\n"]},{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["  Saved: 365 patches\n","\n","Processing 'test' …\n"]},{"output_type":"stream","name":"stderr","text":["test: 100%|██████████| 470/470 [00:18<00:00, 25.55patch/s]\n"]},{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["  Saved: 245 patches\n","\n","✅  Done for the 432 site! Total patches: 2212\n","   train:  1602  (72.4%)\n","   val  :   365  (16.5%)\n","   test :   245  (11.1%)\n","\n","Channels per patch: 30\n","Saved to:     /content/drive/MyDrive/Geoinformatics_Project/NewStructure/data/sites/site-432-tropical-savanna/patches/patches_PS_SENT_432_682\n","\n","For model: UNet(in_channels=30, out_channels=2)\n","PlanetScope: 10124×5219 px, reading bands [2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 8, 9, 10, 11, 12, 13, 14, 15, 16]\n","\n","Reading pre-fire Sentinel-2 …\n","Reading post-fire Sentinel-2 …\n","  S2 channels in stack: 10 (5 pre + 5 post)\n","  S2 Indices in stack: 6  ['NDVI_S2_pre', 'NDVI_S2_post', 'NBR_S2_pre', 'NBR_S2_post', 'dNDVI_S2', 'dNBR_S2']\n","\n","Total channels in stack: 30\n","\n","Rasterizing labels …\n","Unique label values: [  0   1 255]\n","\n","Spatial zones (cols): train=[0,7040)  val=[7040,8576)  test=[8576,10124)\n","\n","Processing 'train' …\n"]},{"output_type":"stream","name":"stderr","text":["train: 100%|██████████| 2200/2200 [01:25<00:00, 25.83patch/s]\n"]},{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["  Saved: 1280 patches\n","\n","Processing 'val' …\n"]},{"output_type":"stream","name":"stderr","text":["val: 100%|██████████| 480/480 [00:19<00:00, 25.07patch/s]\n"]},{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["  Saved: 297 patches\n","\n","Processing 'test' …\n"]},{"output_type":"stream","name":"stderr","text":["test: 100%|██████████| 480/480 [00:15<00:00, 31.80patch/s]\n"]},{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["  Saved: 220 patches\n","\n","✅  Done for the 682 site! Total patches: 1797\n","   train:  1280  (71.2%)\n","   val  :   297  (16.5%)\n","   test :   220  (12.2%)\n","\n","Channels per patch: 30\n","Saved to:     /content/drive/MyDrive/Geoinformatics_Project/NewStructure/data/sites/site-682-tropical-savanna/patches/patches_PS_SENT_432_682\n","\n","For model: UNet(in_channels=30, out_channels=2)\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["##### Contributors:\n","- **Evgenii Miasnikov**: evgenii.miasnikov@mail.polimi.it\n","- **Ayman Mutasim Alfadul Abdelgadir**: aymanmutasim@mail.polimi.it\n","\n","```\n","   Copyright 2026 Evgenii Miasnikov, Ayman Mutasim Alfadul Abdelgadir\n","\n","   Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n","   you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n","   You may obtain a copy of the License at\n","\n","       https://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n","\n","   Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n","   distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n","   WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either ex